  "text": "The nematode Caenorhabditis elegans develops as either a male having only one sex chromosome (XO) in the somatic cells or a hermaphrodite with two sex chromosomes (XX) in the somatic cells (the self-fertile hermaphrodite is essentially a female that produces sperm for a brief period before oogenesis; [CITATION_1] . Gametes with no sex chromosome are generated as a consequence of chromosome nondisjunction during meiosis which is a rather rare event; in wildtype populations, males present only at low (~0.3%) frequency.",
